column1: #Text=Paris, Jan. 15—Charles X. visited the Museum of the Louvre on Friday.
#Text=An address was read to his Majesty, in which he was successively compared to Louis XIV.
#Text=In his reply, the King said the protection of the arts would always be one of the objects most dear to him.
#Text=He then distributed a great many decorations of the Legion of Honour among the painters, sculptors and engravers who were present Our countryman Mr T.
#Text=Lawrence was nominated a Knight of the Legion of Honour.
#Text=Stratford Canning, British Ambassador to the Court of Russia, has had a private audience of the Emperor.
#Text=His ExceUency was above an hour with his Majesty.
#Text=Canning will set out very soon for St, Petersuurgh.
#Text=Count Woronzow Daschkow, Minister Plenipotentiary of Russia at the Court of Bavaria, left this city the day before yesterday, to return to Munich.
#Text=It is affirmed, that the departure of their Imperial Majesties for Italy, is fixed for the month of March; that they will pass the spring at Milan, and part of the summer at Venice.
